      <h1 class='title'>Eritrea</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c254WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_254ws' title='Col. 254WS &mdash; HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c254WS' name='column_254ws' href='#column_254ws' rel='bookmark'>254WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06210'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_229'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-john-barrett' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_229' title='Link to this speech by Mr John Barrett' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-john-barrett" title="Mr John Barrett">John Barrett</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06210">To ask the Secretary of State for International Development what assessment she has made of the numbers of children aged<span class="italic">(a)</span> 1 to 3 and <span class="italic">(b)</span> 4 to 5 years old suffering from malnutrition in Eritrea; and if she will make a statement. [88683]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06211'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_230'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-clare-short' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_230' title='Link to this speech by Ms Clare Short' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-clare-short" title="Ms Clare Short">Clare Short</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06211">We do not have a specific breakdown by age of the number of children suffering from malnutrition in Eritrea. However, UNICEF have reported that, as of July 2002, three out of the six zones of Eritrea were showing levels of malnutrition in children above 15 per cent., and that more recent surveys have shown an increase.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
